article.headline: Memphis 108, Lamar 75
article.story: MEMPHIS, Tenn. -- Antonio Anderson scored 12 points, dished out 13 assists and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Memphis to a 108-75 victory over Lamar on Saturday night. Anderson became only the second Memphis player in history to record a triple-double since Anfernee Hardaway in 1993. Tyreke Evans, who went 11 of 16 from the field, scored 25 points. Robert Dozier finished with 19 points, and Shawn Taggart scored 15 points Doneal Mack had 14 for the Tigers (10-3). Kenny Dawkins led Lamar (9-4) with 19 points, while Brandon McThay contributed 12. Charlie Harper and Tristan Worrell had 11 apiece for the Cardinals. Memphis, which won its fourth straight since a 72-65 loss to Syracuse on Dec. 20, shot 53 percent. Memphis put the game away in the first half, erasing an early Lamar advantage with a 16-0 run.
